What you need to know:  Tergat, who made history as the first man to win five consecutive world cross country titles, served in the same capacity when the event made its fourth journey back to Africa in 2017 in KampalaTergat is one of the greats of long-distance running and it was in cross country that his success story really beganTergat and fellow Ethiopian legendary distance runner Haile Gebrselassie took their Olympic rivalry from 1996 Atlanta to 2000 Sydney where Tergat pushed Gebrselassie all the way before ultimately ending up with silver again